{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013726EiErxLnhZAndkmdzsT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to do a rolling upgrade. The steps are:\n\n1. Update the StatefulSet image to 8.11.1\n2. Since the update strategy is `OnDelete`, I need to delete pods one at a time and wait for each to come back healthy before proceeding to the next\n\nThe approach for Elasticsearch rolling upgrade:\n1. Disable shard allocation before restarting each node to prevent unnecessary data movement\n2. Update image\n3. Delete pods one at a time (starting with non-master)\n4. Wait for each pod to be ready and cluster to be green again before proceeding\n5. I'll execute this systematically by first patching the StatefulSet, then removing pods sequentially and monitoring their recovery before moving to the next one.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":191,"cache_read_input_tokens":32393,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":191},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e3810d9-73ca-49ae-89fb-61553ef1737b","uuid":"c1051ac4-0ef9-4813-bcf1-9f762d85b96d","request_id":"req_011CcMTY8oyXKgf5awB8mZ5X"}
